## Complete Exploration Report: Image-Only AI Providers in Vercel AI SDK

I've thoroughly explored the structure of the Replicate and FAL packages - both image-only AI provider implementations in the Vercel AI SDK monorepo. Here's a complete breakdown:

---

## PACKAGE STRUCTURE OVERVIEW

### Directory Organization
Both packages follow identical structural patterns:
- **packages/replicate/** - For Replicate API integration
- **packages/fal/** - For fal.ai API integration

### Common File Structure
```
packages/{replicate|fal}/
├── src/
│   ├── index.ts (main export barrel)
│   ├── {provider}-provider.ts (provider factory)
│   ├── {provider}-image-model.ts (image generation implementation)
│   ├── {provider}-image-settings.ts (model IDs)
│   ├── {provider}-image-options.ts (provider options schema)
│   ├── {provider}-error.ts (error handling)
│   ├── {provider}-video-model.ts (video generation - if supported)
│   ├── {provider}-video-settings.ts (video model IDs - if supported)
