## KEY PATTERNS & DIFFERENCES

### Replicate (Image-only with Video)
- Simpler structure: Image + Video models
- Uses Bearer token authentication
- Direct API endpoint: `https://api.replicate.com/v1`
- Versioned models support (e.g., `model:version`)
- Synchronous prediction with optional wait time configuration
- Flux-2 models support up to 8 input images

### FAL (Multi-modal)
- Richer structure: Image + Video + Speech + Transcription
- Uses Key-based authentication
- Queue-based system: `https://queue.fal.run` for async operations
- Polling mechanism for job completion
- Comprehensive API type definitions
- Support for language codes, emotions, voice settings
- Deprecation handling for snake_case to camelCase migration

### Common Patterns
- Extends ProviderV3 from @ai-sdk/provider
- Uses Zod schemas for validation
- Error handling with specialized response handlers
- Version injection at build time via __PACKAGE_VERSION__
- Identical npm script structure
- Both node and edge-runtime test configurations
- Full TypeScript with composite project references

